               <p>I took the prisoner filling a bottle: I am cooper to the prosecutors: the prisoner is a smith; I watched the store cellar; the prisoner came in with a stone gallon bottle, and he filled it; I took him to Mr. Pierce's compting-house; I know nothing more: it is Mess. Pierce and Sedgwick's store cellar.</p>
               <p>Mr. Garrow. How came the prisoner to have an opportunity of getting in there? - He lived under the same roof.</p>
               <p>What character does he bear? - A very good one.</p>
